ias what word describes the fear of strangers or foreigners?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich Scottish author who died in 1930 had Ignatius as one of his christian names?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich token in a game of Monopoly was once known as Rich Uncle Pennybags?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nAladdin Sane and Diamond Dogs were number one albums for which famous singer in the 1970's?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nDavid Tyler is the current chairman of which leading supermarket chain?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Which \"\"Carry On\"\" film contained the line 'Oh yes colonel, many times, but never with a daffodil'?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Which actor played the lead role of Jay Gatsby in the 1974 film \"\"the Great Gatsby\"\"\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich other colour, along with yellow and green appears on the flag of Gabon?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Which snooker player had the nickname \"\"The Thunder from Down Under\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Who is the principal actor who plays a character named Michael Blomqvist in the 2011 film \"\"The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nOriginally marketed as a rat poison what is the most commonly used drug in the treatment of thrombosis and embolism?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"What is the name of the short actor who plays the main role in the BBC2 comedy series\"\"Life's too short\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich US state lends its name to a baked pudding, made with ice cream, sponge and meringue?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe human brain is made up of between 10 billion and 100 billion nerve cells known as what?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich microprocessor was introduced by Intel in 1993?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe upper house of the Canadian parliament is known as 