sters and singers Dannii and Kylie?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nJames Esdaile, John Elliotson, Jean-Martin Charcot, Hippolyte Bernheim, Pierre Janet, mile Cou, Morton Prince, Clark L. Hull, Andrew Salter, Theodore R. Sarbin, Ernest Hilgard, Martin Theodore Orne, and Nicholas Spanos are associated with what?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nActress Brooke Shields was married to whom for 2 years from April 1997?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the name of Tony and Cherie Blair's daughter?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich country shares a 530 km border with Saudi Arabia on the west, south, and southeast, a 450 km border with Oman on the southeast and northeast, and a smaller border with Qatar in the northwest?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe lead singer of which band is known as Suggs?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn June 2010, 8 highly endangered monkeys (4 cottontop tamarins and 4 pygmy marmosets) were stolen from the Symbio Wildlife Park in which country?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat term is used for the actress that has the main part in a film or play?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nDishes prepared with spinach can be referred to as what?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat island would you come to first if you travelled due east from Bangladesh?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nAfter the murder of his children's nanny, Sandra Rivett, Richard John Bingham disappeared on 8 November 1974, was presumed deceased on 11 December 1992 and declared legally dead in October 1999. By what name is he better known?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"In what country, between the 1950s and 1980, would one have found \"\"Rusticated Youth\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho is the only US President who did not speak English as his first language?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn which sport is it forbidden for anyone to play left handed?\n\