cean through what?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Which police station is at the centre of the long-running UK TV series \"\"The Bill\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nA tropical plant that grows several feet high, with a large fleshy root that contains an acrid milk juice, poisonous in its natural form, produces from the juice, extracted under pressure and purified, a staple foodstuff called what?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat shape are honeycomb cells?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"After stints backing Little Richard and the Isley Brothers, who was discovered leading \"\"Jimmy James and the Blue Flames\"\" at the Caf Wha? in New York and taken to London on 26 September 1966 to make hit records?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich Earl of Essex, after being sent to Ireland as Governor-General in 1599, being briefly imprisoned and leading a rebellion against Queen Eliabeth I, was executed in 1601?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat novel was published by Bob Dylan in 1971?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nDragon boat racing, as part of a complex of ceremonies, is thought to have originated where?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the name of a device, consisting essentially of two wires of different metals, whereby heat energy may be changed to electrical energy?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Which Bob Dylan song begins \"\"You got a lotta nerveTo say you are my friend. When I was down, You just stood there grinning\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"In Australia, what is known as a \"\"Laughing Jackass\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Which British singer, born Sandra Ann Goodrich, was known as \"\"the barefoot pop princess of the 1960s\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn Central and South America it is possible to find several rivers named Colorado, in Costa Rica, Brazil, Bolivia, Chile, and Argentina; where is the source of the Colorado River in Argentina?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the official language of the People's Republic of Bangladesh?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat word is traditionally applied to clothes and linen collected by a woman before her marriage?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat was the name of the 1976 film that told the story of Woody Guthrie?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Which is the Muppet character who appeared in \"\"The Muppet Show\"\" from the third season and in a number of Muppet films, who throws fish which return to him and plays a fish organ (a line of fish that, when squeezed, each gargle a different note)?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"The name of which animal means \"\"man of the forest\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThis 1993 film won Oscars, Bafta and Golden Globe Awards despite its sometimes harrowing portrayal of hardships and stress, including the butchering of its heroine's hand; which film was it?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Which singer/songwriter, who began releasing hit singles in 1958, has had 3 albums (\"\"The Definitive Collection\"\", \"\"Waking Up Is Hard to Do\"\" & \"\"The Music of My Life\"\") on Billboard's Top 200 Albums chart between 2007 & 2010?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nAccording to a short story by Washington Irving (1819), who escaped his nagging wife by wandering into New York's Catskill Mountains, fell asleep, and returned to his village, where he found that 20 years had passed?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe Indus River flows the length of Pakistan and is Pakistan's main source of water for industry and drinking; where does it rise?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"One of Australia's oldest and most important industrial disputes and the subject of Henry Lawson's poem \"\"Freedom on the Wallaby\"\", in 1891 brought central Queensland to the brink of civil war. What group of people was involved?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nA clapperboard is used in which industry?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe 2013-4 MacRobertson Shield international competition, hosted in New Zealand, was in what sport?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe main international cricket competitions are Test matches, ODI, and which other?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn the culinary world, what word is used for the edible offal of a fowl, typically including the heart, gizzard and liver?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nRedfoo and Sky Blu were members of which electronic rock band?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the name of a book where photographs or stamps are kept?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe third part of trilogy of Hobbit movies, released at the end of 2014, is called what?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nNankey Poo, Poo Bah and Pish Tush are characters in which show?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe cocktail called a Tom Collins consists of lemon or lime juice, sugar, soda water and what else?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nBjrn Ulvaeus and Benny Andersson wrote most of the songs for which pop group?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nMarat, Robespierre, Danton are names associated with what event at the end of the 18th century?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the name of the hand signalling system used by bookmakers to convey horses' odds?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is next in the sequence: Lima, Quito, Bogota...?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe winner of the Academy Award for Best Foreign Film 1987, Babette's Feast, was set in, and filmed by, what country?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat colour cat is a Russian Blue?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nOmar Sharif played the title character in the 1965 film of what 1957 novel by the Russian writer Boris Pasternak?\n\n### Response:\n", "##