n 2006 aim to investigate?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Who published an autobiography entitled \"\"A Journey\"\" on 1 September 2010?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nBritish artist Sir James Thornhill (1675-1734), history painter and sergeant painter to George I and George II, was related by marriage to which other artist?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe largest ice fields in the southern hemisphere outside Antarctica are located where?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat are marram, fescue, and rye?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nJohn Forsythe was a regular in which TV series, but was never seen?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Which Glasgow group signed to Creation Records and recorded their debut single, \"\"All Fall Down\"\", in 1985?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nOn 30 September 1399, Henry Bolingbroke, Duke of Lancaster, became better known as whom?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat links do Bollywood, Hollywood and Lollywood have?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat was the first name of the fictional character Gulliver, which was created by Jonathan Swift?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Which British composer wrote \"\"The Dam Busters March\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn 1483, who was appointed the first grand inquisitor of the Spanish Inquisition?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho was the youngest person to become president of the USA?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nPistol and Boo, who became internationally famous in 2015, were what?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"The song \"\"Sit down, you're rockin' the boat\"\" is from which musical?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Ravel's \"\"Bolero\"\", pop music riffs and (often) suspense music in film soundtracks are examples of what?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Damon Runyon's two stories \"\"The Idyll of Miss Sarah Brown\"\" and \"\"B