ld by Chris Grayling?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich group released their third studio album X+Y in 2005?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich fruit is also known as the alligator pear?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich sport had previously been known as Whiff Whaff and Gossima?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nOn which racecourse is the Welsh Grand National run each December?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho was the main female singer with the groups Jefferson Airplane, Jefferson Starship and Starship?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nAlan Minter was World boxing champion at which weight?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich 1968 film featured the 3rd Foot and Mouth Regiment of soldiers?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn the TV series Doctor Who, who was the creator of the Daleks and arch enemy of the Doctor?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the distinguishing feature of an animal described as \u2018palmiped\u2019?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nTo within a year either side, in which year was the complete English FA Cup Final first shown live on television?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWho painted \u2018Le dejeuner sur I\u2019herbe\u2019 in 1863?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nCanaletto is famous for his landscapes of Venice and which other city?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe 1810 betrothal of Princess Theresa to Crown Prince Ludwig not only resulted in the meadow where the event took place to be named Theresienwiese but also started what?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nA tourist attraction near Alliance, Nebraska created by Jim Reinders using vintage cars is styled after what monument?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe festival of Naadam that features wrestling, archery and horse-racing is an annual event of what land-locked country?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat aspect of the folktale Hansel and Gretel has been adapted in user-interface design to help users navigate among various screens?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nCatoptromancy is the term for predicting the future using what object? Who's the fairest of them all!\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat 1841 invention of the art world that replaced the usage of pig bladders was called by Renoir as indispensable for Impressionism?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn 1914 a paleontologist suggested that what legend might have originated from Greeks interpreting the nasal cavity in the skull of prehistoric dwarf elephants as a large single eye-socket?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nAkira Yoshizawa, to whom Google paid a tribute with a doodle of folded letters on March 14, 2012 is said to have elevated what craft into an art form?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe medieval practice of appointing a cardinal who was a nephew of a pope gives us which English word that means bestowing favors to relatives/friends?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nTypically worn in rural areas while hunting, what type of hat became a stereotypical head wear of a detective because of its association with Sherlock Holmes?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the name given to a sculpted female figure serving as an architectural support taking the place of a column or a pillar?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat type of 'helpful' businesses operate on the basis of the Rochdale Principles that were formulated in 1844?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat product invented by Frederick Walton in 1864 became so widely used and 'stepped on' that the name became generic just 14 years after its invention?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nNamed for a Greek muse and currently given by the Nielsen Company, what are the awards given to reward creative excellence in advertising and design?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe American journalist Ida Tarbell is known for her expose of the corrupt practices of which giant company? John D. Rockefeller probably hated her!\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn the 2014 zombie comedy Life After Beth, a character takes offense when asked about zombies just because she is from what country?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe camera technique of panning and zooming on still photographs often seen in documentaries has come to be known as the effect of what filmmaker?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Commenting on the death of screenwriter Ruth Prawer Jhabvala in April 2013, which film company issued the statement \"\"The passing of our two-time Academy Award winning screenwriter is a significant loss to the global film community.\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe documentary Lousy Little Sixpence (1983) and the feature-film Rabbit-Proof Fence (2002) focus on 'Stolen Generations' in which country?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"\"\"At night they fly, you better run, these winged things are not much fun.\"\" \"\"In the jungle you must wait, until the dice read five or eight.\"\" \"\"A tiny bite can make you itch, make you sneeze, make you twitch.\"\" \"\"This will not be an easy mission, monkeys slow the expedition.\"\" Clues from what 1995 movie game?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nA 2002 article titled What's Sarong with this Picture? in an online film journal profiled which yesteryear actress?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nBill Gold whose most noted creations are for films as varied as Casablanca, A Clockwork Orange, Mystic River and The Sting is renowned for what type of work?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe documentary about the making of which 1970s groundbreaking film was titled Hearts of Darkness alluding not just to the novel that inspired it but also to it's chaotic production?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe Dodecanese Campaign of WWII that was an attempt by the Allied forces to capture islands in the Aegean Sea was the inspiration for which acclaimed 1961 commando film?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat 2009 hit that rewarded a woman director opens with the quotation 'The rush of battle is a potent and often lethal addiction, for war is a drug'?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"In a 2007 interview, which actor 'animatedly' bemoaned \"\"I hate that cat! Ever since I did that cat, I disappear. It's all about the cat. It stole everything from me.\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nMammy Two Shoes, a recurring character in MGM's Tom and Jerry cartoons was inspired by which African-American actress and singer?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat period film of Stanley Kubrick that recounts the exploits of an 18th century Irish adventurer is loosely based on a novel of William Makepeace Thackeray?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn which award winning 1990 movie is much of the dialog in the Lakota language?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat food staple is the focus of a 1980 documentary ___ Is as Good as Ten Mothers that was filmed primarily in Gilroy, California?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the second-largest day for U.S. food consumption, after Thanksgiving Day?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich sauce made from ham drippings and coffee and seen in the cuisine of the Southern United States gets its name from its appearance like that of a certain body organ?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich crop that was of great nutritional importance in pre-Columbian Andean civilizations, and which has now entered the mainstream world market, was called as the 'mother of all grains' by the Incas?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Didier Delsalle who wrote the following words confirming his May 14, 2005 achievement became the first person to land a helicopter where? \"\"No, nobody went out of the helicopter as I was alone and quite busy to stabilize the helicopter on this windy ...! The terrain characteristics prevent any full landing on the ... as you can see on the videos and only a hover landing...\"\"\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn 2014, CNN reported that FBI and other law enforcement agencies send their trainees to what Washington, D.C. museum so they can see for themselves how not protecting civil liberties can lead to bigger horrors?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIf Aman handles military intelligence and Shin Bet handles internal security, which agency is responsible for the overseas intelligence work of its country?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nBran Castle that is located on the border between Transylvania and Wallachia in Romania is marketed as the home of which sinister figure?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nUsed to describe US citizens who attempted to foment insurrections in Latin America in the mid-19th century, what is the term for someone who engages in an unauthorized military expedition into a foreign country to support a revolution?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhose summer residence is at Lake Gandalfo, a small town south-east of Rome?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn the Norrmalmstorg bank robbery in 1973, employees were held hostage for a few days and became emotionally attached to their captors, and even defended them after they were freed from their six-day ordeal. In which city did this incident take place?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich organization of the Catholic church whose name is Latin for 'Work of God' received world attention with the publication of The Da Vinci Code in which it is portrayed as participating in a sinister international conspiracy?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe organization Medecins Sans Frontieres (Doctors without Borders) was created in 1971 as an aftermath of what humanitarian crisis in Africa?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe Frenchman Jean Robert-