Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nAn urban legend about the similarity in the flags of Bahrain and what other country says that the red color of Bahrain weathered in the sun into the maroon of the other?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat 3-word phrase used to denote unexplored territories derives from the medieval practice of putting sea serpents in uncharted areas of maps?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nMohenjo-daro and Harappa in present-day Pakistan were the most important city settlements of a Bronze Age civilization that is named after what major geographic feature?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIf the Staten Island Ferry is to New York, the Star Ferry that was originally called the Kowloon Ferry Company is to what city?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat are the table-top mountains found in the Guiana Highlands of South America (especially Venezuela) that inspired Arthur Conan Doyle's The Lost World and also appear prominently in the landscapes of the Pixar hit Up?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich Japanese island that has its capital at Sapporo is the traditional home of the Ainu people?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe Bridge of the Horns is a proposed construction project to build a bridge across the Bab-el-Mandeb, the strait between the Red Sea and Gulf of Aden. What two countries will it connect?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the only language that is historically African in origin among the six official working languages of the African Union?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nA 'triskelion', a symbol consisting of three bent human legs is featured on the flag of which British crown dependency?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich country is separated into two parts by the town of Limbang of Malaysia?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe flag of which country prominently features 'The Eagle of Saladin' holding a scroll bearing the name of the country in Arabic?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nLuzon, Visayas and Mindanao form the three major island groups of which country?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the largest country with a single time zone?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich city in Egypt has been characterised as the 'world's greatest open air museum' and contains the ruins of the temple complexes at Karnak as well as monuments that include the Valley of the Kings and the Valley of the Queens?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich island in the Mediterranean was the center of the Minoan civilization (ca. 2600-1400 BCE), the oldest civilization in Europe?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"The No. 617 Squadron of the Royal Air Force which operated with the motto \"\"After me, the flood\"\" is known for its attacks on what type of installations during WWII?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe 1938 work The Black Jacobins by C. L. R. James is an account of what upheaval that took place between 1791 and 1804?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat battle of the Middle Ages fought on Saint Crispin's Day has been immortalized by a speech that references the day in a Shakespearean history play?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich country is currently ruled by the Chakri dynasty that has been in power since 1782?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe Battle of Kadesh in 1274 BC that took place between the forces of the Egyptian Empire under Ramesses II and the Hittite Empire is best known for the use of what type of vehicles?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe 1827 Battle of Navarino in which the Ottoman/Egyptian armada was destroyed by a combined British, French and Russian navy is notable for being the last battle to be fought with sailing ships. It is a conflict in the war of independence of which country?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nAfter a short war with Norway during the Napoleonic wars of 1814, what country remained uninvolved in any conflict ever since and is now the oldest neutral country in the world?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe Battle of Asculum took place in 279 BC between the Romans and the Greeks in which the Romans lost 6,000 men, while the Greeks lost 3,500, including many of their officers. Who commanded the 'victorious' Greeks?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe Battle of the Plains of Abraham in 1759, a pivotal battle in the Seven Years' War fought between the English and the French, is the only major confrontation ever to have taken place in what country?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich city of central Spain was renowned throughout the Middle Ages as an important center for the production of swords and other bladed instruments?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe 1997 transfer of Hong Kong from Great Britain to China is well-known. But in 1999, which country similarly relinquished its claim on Macau also handing it over to China?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhen it was liberated from the UK in 1957, which country became the first sub-Saharan nation to gain independence?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nLapine, which is derived from the French word for rabbit, is the language spoken by the characters of what 1972 novel?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe 19th century invention Paige Compositor sought to replace the typewriter but ended up becoming a failure. Which American author lost nearly all his fortune for its development?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the name of the vessel in Paul Gallico's 1969 adventure novel that has been adapted as a film four times?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe division of Penguin that deals with science fiction and fantasy books started in 2002 with what fantastical avian name? (hint: Stravinsky)\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the subject of the best-known works of writers Theodor Mommsen and Edward Gibbon?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nGreat short-stories like The Gift of the Magi, The Ransom of Red Chief, and The Cop and the Anthem are from what collection of O. Henry that was a reaction to a statement that only four hundred people mattered in New York?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe 1968 children's story Tikki Tikki Tembo by Arlene Mosel is a humorous take on the perils of what?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nA fictional species of great apes called 'Mangani' are responsible for raising which popular character?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe first name of which science fiction hero created by Alex Raymond was retitled as 'Speed' in Australia to avoid a negative connotation of the word by which we know him better?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWashington Irving's classic story Rip Van Winkle is set in which geographic region of New York state?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"The 1902 guitar composition \"\"Gran Vals\"\" by the Spanish composer Francisco T\u00e1rrega would have remained obscure but for corporate executive Anssi Vanjoki selecting it for something in 1993. How do millions of people recognize it now?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich 1977 musical was inspired by a magazine article about Bay Ridge kids of Brooklyn whose working class lives were said to be so empty that they lived just to dance on the weekend?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe lyrics of which song first put to music by Pete Seeger in 1959 and later made famous by The Byrds were taken almost entirely from the Book of Ecclesiastes in the Bible?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich rock concert held on December 6, 1969 was speculated to be a 'Woodstock West' but became infamous after it was marred by considerable violence?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the name of the coronation anthem composed by Handel using texts from the King James Bible that has been sung at every British coronation service since 1727?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich 1968 album released by George Harrison is notable for being the first official solo album by one of The Beatles?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich 1989 music video of Madonna attracted criticism for showing images like her making love to Saint Martin de Porres, use of Catholic iconography including a scene where she develops stigmata as well as cross burning?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the better known name of the English singer Yusuf Islam who converted to Islam in 1977 at the height of his fame?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"'The Doors' generated a controversy with the single \"\"Hello, I Love You\"\" in 1968 when the press pointed out it's resemblance to the 1965 hit \"\"All Day and All of the Night\"\" of which band?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nJimi Hendrix presented the broken parts of the guitar that he destroyed on-stage at the 1968 Miami Pop Festival to whom? Not sure if the recipient named it Moon Unit.\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWardenclyffe Tower in Shoreham, New York was designed by which genius who intended to showcase it for demonstrations of wireless power transmission?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nSt Thomas's Abbey, Brno in the Czech Republic was the scene of whose path-breaking work from 1856 to 1863?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat is the last name name of the doctor who first described a certain disease in An Essay on the Shaking Palsy written in 1817?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe Hubble sequence that classifies galaxies is also known for being drawn in what shape?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe bitter 19th century rivalry between paleontologists Edward Drinker Cope and Othniel Charles Marsh during their search for dinosaur fossils is usually described with what 2-words?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nScientist Ernest Rutherford once said 