r order in the animal kingdom?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nA 'Captcha' test that usually requires a user to identify and type letters/digits from a distorted image is an attempt to ensure that a response is not generated by a computer. It is also described as a reverse what test?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nIn metallurgy, the term 'rouging' refers to a form of corrosion found on what substance that you do not readily associate with corrosion?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhich acid that makes up 55-80% of olive oil is also emitted by decaying bee corpses thus triggering the instincts of living bees to remove dead bees from their hives?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThough it is the most abundant metallic element in Earth's crust, which element is very rare in its free form and once prompted Napoleon III, Emperor of France to give a banquet where the most honoured guests were given utensils made of it while the 'lesser' guests had to make do with gold!\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"Sportscaster Jack Brickhouse who once said \"\"Any team can have a bad century\"\" provided play-by-play coverage of what American major league team's games from 1948 to 1981?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\n\"The name of what tennis star was used by a commentator for the the hole cards Ace\u2013King (unsuited) of Texas Hold 'em as they meet the criteria of \"\"looks great but never wins\"\"?\"\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nSummer Olympic sports are divided into categories based on popularity and the potential in generating revenue. As of 2014, only 3 sports are in Category A. They are athletics, aquatics, and what else?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nThe Peck and Snyder are sometimes considered the first of what sporting collectibles?\n\n### Response:\n", "### Instruction:\nWhat American city has suffered two (separate) outcomes of what are now called 'The Move' and 'The Decision' in sports lore?\n\n### 